139
00:07:31,959 --> 00:07:32,480
Spare me, hero!

140
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:32,879
Please, have mercy!

141
00:07:33,160 --> 00:07:34,000
I don't know anything.

142
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,319
I don't know.

143
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:38,800
Young Master Meng

144
00:07:40,079 --> 00:07:40,879
You are...

145
00:07:41,399 --> 00:07:42,160
Master

146
00:07:42,160 --> 00:07:43,279
It's me, Master.

147
00:07:43,399 --> 00:07:44,600
I used to help in your kitchen.

148
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:45,439
When you were little,

149
00:07:45,439 --> 00:07:46,920
you loved my date pastries the most.

150
00:07:47,759 --> 00:07:48,600
Oh.

151
00:07:48,959 --> 00:07:50,519
So it was you.

152
00:07:50,959 --> 00:07:52,199
If you hadn't said anything,

153
00:07:52,199 --> 00:07:53,399
I wouldn't have remembered.

154
00:07:54,199 --> 00:07:54,839
It was you.

155
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:57,600
You never cleaned out the pits.

156
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:59,279
I always bit down on them.

157
00:08:01,399 --> 00:08:02,199
Speak.

158
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:04,439
My family's Mo Fei jade—

159
00:08:04,439 --> 00:08:06,160
Did you sell it to the auction house?

160
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:08,319
Master, what are you saying?

161
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:09,519
I don't know.

162
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:11,959
Where did you find him?

163
00:08:13,399 --> 00:08:14,720
At an auction.

164
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:17,199
I heard Meng family items were up for sale.

165
00:08:17,199 --> 00:08:18,120
So I went there.

166
00:08:18,759 --> 00:08:20,399
Didn't expect him to show up too.

167
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:26,079
He's been hiding all these years.

168
00:08:27,160 --> 00:08:28,399
He must've suffered a lot.

169
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:31,399
So I don't blame him for acting that way.

170
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,799
You know what I can do, right?

171
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:36,799
You really want to force me?

172
00:08:38,159 --> 00:08:39,360
Let me warn you—

173
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,720
I'm not that skilled with this trick yet.

174
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,000
Still not very practiced.

175
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,759
If I use it on you,

176
00:08:43,759 --> 00:08:45,159
you might have side effects.

177
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:48,120
Like brain damage,

178
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:49,320
paralysis,

179
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:50,639
or losing control of your bladder.

180
00:08:50,639 --> 00:08:50,919
No!

181
00:08:50,919 --> 00:08:53,000
Don't say I didn't warn you.

182
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:54,720
No!

183
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:56,679
I know the Meng family's ways.

184
00:08:56,799 --> 00:08:58,399
I'll talk.

185
00:08:59,919 --> 00:09:00,720
Speak up!

186
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:02,320
It was that night.

187
00:09:02,919 --> 00:09:03,200
I...

188
00:09:03,639 --> 00:09:04,519
I stole it.

189
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:05,799
That night.

190
00:09:07,399 --> 00:09:08,960
You were there the night my family was killed.

191
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:12,679
I should've left earlier that night.

192
00:09:13,159 --> 00:09:14,960
But the date pastries weren't done.

193
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:17,279
The chef made me redo a batch.

194
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:19,120
I fell asleep under the stove.

195
00:09:19,679 --> 00:09:22,120
When I woke up, there was chaos outside.

196
00:09:22,399 --> 00:09:23,759
I didn't know what was happening.

197
00:09:24,399 --> 00:09:25,399
I went out to look—

198
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:26,759
There were bodies everywhere.

199
00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:28,000
Blood everywhere.

200
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:31,480
I figured the master and madam were gone.

201
00:09:31,799 --> 00:09:33,799
The Meng family was finished.

202
00:09:34,159 --> 00:09:37,399
So I thought, no one wanted the stuff.

203
00:09:37,799 --> 00:09:39,600
I took whatever I could.

204
00:09:39,799 --> 00:09:42,320
Gambled it all away over the years.

205
00:09:42,399 --> 00:09:43,679
Only that was left.

206
00:09:43,879 --> 00:09:46,519
But I lost too much lately.

207
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:48,000
So I sold it too.

208
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:49,600
Who bought it?

209
00:09:50,159 --> 00:09:51,559
The auction house owner.

210
00:09:51,559 --> 00:09:52,799
He looked like bad news.

211
00:09:53,399 --> 00:09:54,279
No one else.

212
00:09:55,679 --> 00:09:56,039
That's it.

213
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:57,159
Just him.

214
00:09:57,720 --> 00:09:59,360
If you don't believe me, check yourself.

215
00:09:59,679 --> 00:10:00,600
I know you Meng family folks

216
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,679
can read minds.

217
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:03,200
Nothing gets past you.

218
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:07,159
I remember when his family had trouble,

219
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:09,360
my dad suddenly insisted

220
00:10:09,399 --> 00:10:11,200
I go north to visit my uncle.

221
00:10:11,919 --> 00:10:13,480
When I came back,

222
00:10:13,799 --> 00:10:15,360
his house was empty.

223
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:17,399
So I think

224
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:18,960
what happened to his family—

225
00:10:19,759 --> 00:10:20,879
our elders

226
00:10:20,879 --> 00:10:22,000
must've known.

227
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:25,559
Me too.

228
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:29,200
Just days before his family fell,

229
00:10:29,759 --> 00:10:30,840
my mom suddenly asked

230
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,080
if I wanted to study abroad.

231
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,200
When he needed us most,

232
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,000
none of us were there.

233
00:10:36,799 --> 00:10:38,480
No wonder he's so disappointed in us.

234
00:10:39,320 --> 00:10:40,759
My family treated you well, right?

235
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:43,200
When my family was attacked,

236
00:10:44,159 --> 00:10:45,399
you just watched.

237
00:10:46,159 --> 00:10:46,960
Master.

238
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:48,720
Those people killed everyone they saw.

239
00:10:48,799 --> 00:10:50,320
No one survived.

240
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:51,960
If I hadn't hidden under the stove,

241
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:53,600
I'd be dead too.

242
00:10:53,919 --> 00:10:55,519
Even Aunt Cheng, the cleaner—

243
00:10:55,679 --> 00:10:57,559
half her body was gone.

244
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:58,559
Wait.

245
00:10:59,759 --> 00:11:01,480
You said those people—

246
00:11:03,279 --> 00:11:04,320
Who else was there?

247
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:06,720
Do you remember how many?

248
00:11:06,919 --> 00:11:07,759
I don't remember.

249
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:09,200
Will you talk or not?

250
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:10,200
Master.

251
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:11,559
It's not that I won't talk.

252
00:11:11,559 --> 00:11:12,879
I really didn't see.

253
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:15,200
I just remember one person—

254
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:17,519
No, not a person.

255
00:11:17,519 --> 00:11:18,559
It was a Monster.

256
00:11:18,559 --> 00:11:19,399
It had no arms.

257
00:11:19,519 --> 00:11:21,159
A blade grew from its arm.

258
00:11:21,679 --> 00:11:22,320
A blade.

259
00:11:22,799 --> 00:11:23,679
Master.

260
00:11:23,679 --> 00:11:26,000
That Monster is right behind you.
